Abies nordmanniana.label: Abies nordmanniana
Abies nordmanniana.description: Abies nordmanniana, the Nordmann Fir, is a fir native to the mountains west and east of the Black Sea, in Turkey, Georgia, Russian Caucasus and northern parts of Armenia. Wikipedia

Abies nebrodensis.label: Abies nebrodensis
Abies nebrodensis.description: Sicilian Fir is a fir native to the Nebrodi and Madonie mountains in northern Sicily. It is a medium-size evergreen coniferous tree growing to 15–25 m tall and with a trunk diameter of up to 1 m. It occurs at altitudes of 1400-1,600 m. Wikipedia

Afrocarpus.label: Afrocarpus
Afrocarpus.description: Afrocarpus is a genus of conifers belonging to the podocarp family Podocarpaceae. Afrocarpus was designated a genus in 1989, when several species formerly classified in Podocarpus and Nageia were reclassified. Two to six species are recognized. Wikipedia

Agathis australis.label: Agathis australis
Agathis australis.description: Agathis australis, commonly known by its Māori name kauri, is a coniferous tree of Araucariaceae in the genus Agathis, found north of 38°S in the northern districts of New Zealand's North Island. Wikipedia

Araucaria.label: Araucaria
Araucaria.description: Araucaria is a genus of evergreen coniferous trees in the family Araucariaceae. There are 19 extant species in the genus, with a Gondwanan natural distribution in New Caledonia, Norfolk Island, eastern ... Wikipedia

Araucaria araucana.label: Monkey puzzle tree
Araucaria araucana.description: Araucaria araucana is an evergreen tree growing to 40 m tall with a 2-m trunk diameter. The tree is native to central and southern Chile and western Argentina. Araucaria araucana is the hardiest species in the conifer genus Araucaria. Wikipedia

Athrotaxis.label: Athrotaxis
Athrotaxis.description: Athrotaxis is a genus of two to three species of conifers in the cypress family, Cupressaceae. The genus is endemic to western Tasmania, where they grow in high altitude temperate rainforests. Wikipedia

Callitris.label: Callitris
Callitris.description: Callitris is a genus of coniferous trees in the Cupressaceae. There are 15 species in the genus, of which 13 are native to Australia and the other two native to New Caledonia. Wikipedia

Calocedrus.label: Calocedrus
Calocedrus.description: Calocedrus is a genus of four species of coniferous trees in the cypress family Cupressaceae. The generic name means "beautiful cedar". Wikipedia

Cephalotaxus harringtonia.label: Cephalotaxus harringtonia
Cephalotaxus harringtonia.description: Cephalotaxus harringtonii, commonly known as Cowtail Pine or Japanese Plum Yew, is a coniferous bush or small tree in the plum yew family. Wikipedia

Colorado Pinyon.label: Pinus edulis
Colorado Pinyon.description: Pinus edulis, the Colorado pinyon, two-needle pinyon, or piñon pine, is a pine in the pinyon pine group whose ancestor was a member of the Madro-Tertiary Geoflora and is native to the United States. Wikipedia

Coulter Pine.label: Coulter pine
Coulter Pine.description: The Coulter pine or big-cone pine, Pinus coulteri, is a native of the coastal mountains of Southern California and northern Baja California. Wikipedia

Cryptomeria.label: Cryptomeria
Cryptomeria.description: Cryptomeria is a monotypic genus of conifer in the cypress family Cupressaceae, formerly belonging to the family Taxodiaceae. It includes only one species, Cryptomeria japonica. It is endemic to Japan, where it is known as Sugi. Wikipedia

Dacrydium.label: Dacrydium
Dacrydium.description: Dacrydium is a genus of conifers belonging to the podocarp family Podocarpaceae. Sixteen species of evergreen dioecious trees and shrubs are presently recognized. Wikipedia

Cupressus bakeri.label: Cupressus bakeri
Cupressus bakeri.description: Cupressus bakeri, the Modoc cypress, Siskiyou cypress or Baker cypress, is a species of cypress native to a small area in the western United States, located in California and Oregon. Wikipedia

Halocarpus.label: Halocarpus
Halocarpus.description: Halocarpus is a genus of conifers belonging to the Podocarp family Podocarpaceae. The genus includes three closely related species of evergreen trees and shrubs, all endemic to New Zealand. Wikipedia

Jack Pine.label: Jack pine
Jack Pine.description: Jack pine, Pinus banksiana, is an eastern North American pine. Its native range in Canada is east of the Rocky Mountains from Northwest Territories to Nova Scotia, and the north-central and northeast ... Wikipedia

Larix gmelinii.label: Larix gmelinii
Larix gmelinii.description: Dahurian Larch, Larix gmelinii, is a species of larch native to eastern Siberia and adjacent northeastern Mongolia, northeastern China and North Korea. Wikipedia

Larix laricina.label: Larix laricina
Larix laricina.description: Larix laricina, commonly known as the tamarack, hackmatack eastern larch, black larch, red larch, or American larch, is a species of larch native to Canada, from eastern Yukon and Inuvik, Northwest ... Wikipedia

Lepidothamnus.label: Lepidothamnus
Lepidothamnus.description: Lepidothamnus is a genus of conifers belonging to the podocarp family Podocarpaceae. The genus includes three species of dioecious evergreen trees and shrubs, and creepers. L. intermedius and L. laxifolius are native to New Zealand. Wikipedia

Leyland Cypress.label: Leyland cypress
Leyland Cypress.description: The Leyland cypress, Cupressus × leylandii, often referred to simply as leylandii, is a fast-growing coniferous evergreen tree much used in horticulture, primarily for hedges and screens. Wikipedia

Libocedrus.label: Libocedrus
Libocedrus.description: Libocedrus is a genus of five species of coniferous trees in the cypress family Cupressaceae, native to New Zealand and New Caledonia. Wikipedia

Microcachrys.label: Microcachrys
Microcachrys.description: Microcachrys tetragona is a species of dioecious conifers belonging to the podocarp family. It is the sole species of the genus Microcachrys. The plant is endemic to western Tasmania, where it is a low shrub growing to 1 m tall at high altitudes. Wikipedia

Nothotsuga.label: Nothotsuga
Nothotsuga.description: Nothotsuga is a genus of coniferous trees in the family Pinaceae, in many respects intermediate between the genera Keteleeria and Tsuga. Wikipedia

Microstrobos.label: Microstrobos
Microstrobos.description: Microstrobos is a genus of plant belonging to the podocarp family. Its name comes from Greek. It has 2 species, which are evergreen dioecious shrubs. Wikipedia

Pinus aristata.label: Pinus aristata
Pinus aristata.description: Pinus aristata, the Rocky Mountain bristlecone pine, is a species of pine native to the United States. It appears in the Rocky Mountains in Colorado and northern New Mexico, with an isolated population in the San Francisco Peaks in Arizona. Wikipedia

Pinus culminicola.label: Pinus culminicola
Pinus culminicola.description: Pinus culminicola, commonly known as Potosi pinyon, is a pine in the pinyon pine group, native and endemic to northeast Mexico. Wikipedia

Pinus ponderosa.label: Pinus ponderosa
Pinus ponderosa.description: Pinus ponderosa, commonly known as the ponderosa pine, bull pine, blackjack pine, or western yellow pine, is a very large pine tree of variable habit native to western United States and Canada. Wikipedia

Pinus longaeva.label: Pinus longaeva
Pinus longaeva.description: Pinus longaeva, the Great Basin bristlecone pine, is a long-living species of tree found in the higher mountains of the southwest United States. Wikipedia

Pitch Pine.label: Pinus rigida
Pitch Pine.description: Pinus rigida, pitch pine, is a small-to-medium sized pine, native to eastern North America. This species occasionally hybridizes with other pine species such as loblolly pine, shortleaf pine, and pond ... Wikipedia

Podocarpus.label: Podocarpus
Podocarpus.description: Podocarpus is a genus of conifers, the most numerous and widely distributed of the podocarp family, Podocarpaceae. Podocarpus are evergreen shrubs or trees usually from 1 to 25 meters tall, known to reach 40 meters at times. Wikipedia

Saxegothaea.label: Saxegothaea
Saxegothaea.description: Saxegothaea is a genus comprising a single species of conifer belonging to the podocarp family Podocarpaceae, its full scientific name is Saxegothaea conspicua, native to southern South America. Wikipedia

Sundacarpus.label: Sundacarpus
Sundacarpus.description: Sundacarpus is a genus of conifers containing a single species Sundacarpus amarus, belonging to the family Podocarpaceae. Wikipedia

Thuja plicata.label: Thuja plicata
Thuja plicata.description: Thuja plicata, commonly called western or Pacific redcedar, giant or western arborvitae, giant cedar, or shinglewood, is a species of Thuja, an evergreen coniferous tree in the cypress family Cupressaceae native to western North America. Wikipedia

Swiss Pine.label: Pinus cembra
Swiss Pine.description: Pinus cembra, also known as Swiss pine, Swiss stone pine or Arolla pine, is a species of pine tree that grows in the Alps and Carpathian Mountains of central Europe, in Poland, Switzerland, France, ... Wikipedia

Thuja sutchuenensis.label: Thuja sutchuenensis
Thuja sutchuenensis.description: Thuja sutchuenensis is a species of thuja, an evergreen coniferous tree in the cypress family Cupressaceae. It is native to China, where it is a critically endangered local endemic in Chengkou County, on the southern slope of the Daba Mountains. Wikipedia

Thujopsis.label: Thujopsis
Thujopsis.description: Thujopsis is a conifer in the cypress family, the sole member of the genus being Thujopsis dolabrata. It is endemic to Japan, where it is named asunaro. Wikipedia

Tsuga heterophylla.label: Tsuga heterophylla
Tsuga heterophylla.description: Tsuga heterophylla, the western hemlock, is a species of hemlock native to the west coast of North America, with its northwestern limit on the Kenai Peninsula, Alaska, and its southeastern limit in northern Sonoma County, California. Wikipedia

Whitebark Pine.label: Pinus albicaulis
Whitebark Pine.description: Pinus albicaulis, with many common names including whitebark pine, white pine, pitch pine, scrub pine, and creeping pine, occurs in the mountains of the Western United States and Canada, specifically ... Wikipedia

Abies alba.label: Abies alba
Abies alba.description: Abies alba, the silver fir or European silver fir, is a fir native to the mountains of Europe, from the Pyrenees north to Normandy, east to the Alps and the Carpathians, Slovenia, Croatia, Bosnia and ... Wikipedia

Cupressus.label: Cupressus
Cupressus.description: The genus Cupressus is one of several genera within the family Cupressaceae that have the common name cypress; for the others, see cypress. It is considered a polyphyletic group. Wikipedia

Cupressus sempervirens.label: Cupressus sempervirens
Cupressus sempervirens.description: Cupressus sempervirens, the Mediterranean Cypress is a species of cypress native to the eastern Mediterranean region, in northeast Libya, southern Albania, southeast Greece, southern Turkey, Cyprus, ... Wikipedia

Keteleeria.label: Keteleeria
Keteleeria.description: Keteleeria is a genus of three species of coniferous trees in the family Pinaceae, related to the genera Nothotsuga and Pseudolarix. Wikipedia

Larix sibirica.label: Larix sibirica
Larix sibirica.description: The Siberian Larch or Russian Larch is a frost-hardy tree native to western Russia, from close to the Finnish border east to the Yenisei valley in central Siberia, where it hybridises with the Dahurian ... Wikipedia

Mountain Pine.label: Pinus mugo
Mountain Pine.description: Pinus mugo, known as mountain pine, dwarf mountain pine, scrub mountain pine, Swiss mountain pine, mugo pine or creeping pine, is a species of conifer, native to high elevation habitats from southwestern to Central Europe. Wikipedia

Pinophyta.label: Pinophyta
Pinophyta.description: The conifers, division Pinophyta, also known as division Coniferophyta or Coniferae, are one of 13 or 14 division-level taxa within the Kingdom Plantae. Pinophytes are gymnosperms. Wikipedia

Pinus canariensis.label: Pinus canariensis
Pinus canariensis.description: Pinus canariensis, the Canary Island pine, is a species in the genus Pinus, family Pinaceae, native and endemic to the outer Canary Islands in the Atlantic Ocean. Wikipedia

Pinus halepensis.label: Pinus halepensis
Pinus halepensis.description: Pinus halepensis, commonly known as the Aleppo Pine, is a pine native to the Mediterranean region. Their range extends from Morocco and Spain north to southern France, Italy and Croatia, and east to ... Wikipedia

Pinus palustris.label: Pinus palustris
Pinus palustris.description: Pinus palustris, commonly known as the Longleaf Pine, is a pine native to the southeastern United States, found along the coastal plain from eastern Texas to southeast Virginia, extending into northern and central Florida. Wikipedia

Pinus wallichiana.label: Pinus wallichiana
Pinus wallichiana.description: Pinus wallichiana is a coniferous evergreen tree native to the Himalaya, Karakoram and Hindu Kush mountains, from eastern Afghanistan east across northern Pakistan and India to Yunnan in southwest China. Wikipedia

Sciadopitys.label: Sciadopitys
Sciadopitys.description: Sciadopitys verticillata, koyamaki, or Japanese umbrella-pine, is a unique conifer endemic to Japan. Wikipedia

Scots Pine.label: Scots pine
Scots Pine.description: Scots pine is a species of pine native to Europe and Asia, ranging from Scotland, Ireland and Portugal in the west, east to eastern Siberia, south to the Caucasus Mountains, and north to well inside the Arctic Circle in Scandinavia. Wikipedia

Sequoia sempervirens.label: Sequoia sempervirens
Sequoia sempervirens.description: Sequoia sempervirens is the sole living species of the genus Sequoia in the cypress family Cupressaceae. Common names include coast redwood, California redwood, and giant redwood. Wikipedia

Stone Pine.label: Stone pine
Stone Pine.description: The stone pine, also called Italian stone pine, umbrella pine and parasol pine, is a tree from the pine family. The tree is native to the Mediterranean region, occurring in Southern Europe, North Africa, and the Levant. Wikipedia

Taxus baccata.label: Taxus baccata
Taxus baccata.description: Taxus baccata is a conifer [native to western, central and southern Europe, northwest Africa, northern Iran and southwest Asia. Wikipedia

Abies nephrolepis.label: Abies nephrolepis
Abies nephrolepis.description: Abies nephrolepis is a species of fir native to northeastern China, North Korea, South Korea, and southeastern Russia. Wikipedia

Abies ziyuanensis.label: Abies ziyuanensis
Abies ziyuanensis.description: Abies ziyuanensis is a species of fir, a conifer in the Pinaceae family. It is only known from four locations in Guangxi and Hunan provinces in China. A. ziyuanensis is related to Abies beshanzuensis, another threatened fir endemic to China. Wikipedia

Afrocarpus falcatus.label: Afrocarpus falcatus
Afrocarpus falcatus.description: Afrocarpus falcatus is a species of tree in the family Podocarpaceae. It is native to the montane forests of southern Africa, where it is distributed in Malawi, Mozambique, South Africa, and Swaziland. Wikipedia

Amentotaxus formosana.label: Amentotaxus formosana
Amentotaxus formosana.description: Taiwan Catkin Yew, Amentotaxus formosana, is a species of conifer in the Taxaceae family. It is a small tree to 10 m tall, with a slender trunk. It was previously recognised as a variant of Amentotaxus argotaenia. Wikipedia

Araucaria bernieri.label: Araucaria bernieri
Araucaria bernieri.description: Araucaria bernieri is a species of conifer in the Araucariaceae family. It is found only in New Caledonia. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Araucaria subulata.label: Araucaria subulata
Araucaria subulata.description: Araucaria subulata is a species of conifer in the Araucariaceae family. It is found only in New Caledonia. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Afrocarpus gracilior.label: Afrocarpus gracilior
Afrocarpus gracilior.description: Afrocarpus gracilior is an evergreen coniferous tree native to the Afromontane forests of Ethiopia, Kenya, Tanzania, and Uganda, growing at 1,800-2,400 m altitude. Wikipedia

Araucaria schmidii.label: Araucaria schmidii
Araucaria schmidii.description: Araucaria schmidii is a species of conifer in the Araucariaceae family. It is found only in New Caledonia. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Araucaria muelleri.label: Araucaria muelleri
Araucaria muelleri.description: Araucaria muelleri is a species of conifer in the Araucariaceae family. It is found only in New Caledonia. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Araucaria cunninghamii.label: Araucaria cunninghamii
Araucaria cunninghamii.description: Araucaria cunninghamii is a species of Araucaria known as hoop pine. Other less commonly used names include colonial pine and Queensland pine. Wikipedia

Araucaria nemorosa.label: Araucaria nemorosa
Araucaria nemorosa.description: Araucaria nemorosa is a species of conifer in the Araucariaceae family. It is found only in New Caledonia, an island possession of France in the South Pacific. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Fraser Fir.label: Fraser Fir
Fraser Fir.description: Fraser Fir is a species of fir native to the mountains of the eastern United States. It is closely related to Balsam Fir, of which it has occasionally been treated as a subspecies or a variety. Wikipedia

Halocarpus bidwillii.label: Halocarpus bidwillii
Halocarpus bidwillii.description: Halocarpus bidwillii is a species of conifer in the family Podocarpaceae. It is native to New Zealand and grows from Coromandel to the extreme south; as the latitude increases, it is found at lower altitudes. Wikipedia

Cordaitales.label: Cordaitales
Cordaitales.description: Cordaitales are an extinct order of woody plants that may have been early conifers, or which may have given rise to the conifers, ginkgos and cycads. They had cone-like reproductive structures reminiscent of those of modern conifers. Wikipedia

Austrocedrus.label: Austrocedrus
Austrocedrus.description: Austrocedrus is a genus of conifer belonging to the cypress family Cupressaceae. It has only one species, Austrocedrus chilensis, native to the Valdivian temperate rain forests and the adjacent drier ... Wikipedia

Huangshan Pine.label: Pinus hwangshanensis
Huangshan Pine.description: Pinus hwangshanensis, or Huangshan pine, is a pine endemic to the mountains of eastern China, in the provinces of Anhui, Fujian, Guizhou, Hubei, Hunan, Jiangxi, and Zhejiang; it is named after the ... Wikipedia

Juniperus excelsa.label: Juniperus excelsa
Juniperus excelsa.description: Juniperus excelsa, commonly called the Greek Juniper, is a juniper found throughout the eastern Mediterranean, from northeastern Greece and southern Bulgaria across Turkey to Syria and Lebanon, and the Caucasus mountains. Wikipedia

Juniperus angosturana.label: Juniperus angosturana
Juniperus angosturana.description: Juniperus angosturana is a species of conifer in the Cupressaceae family. It is found only in Mexico. Wikipedia

Khasi Pine.label: Pinus kesiya
Khasi Pine.description: Pinus kesiya, or Khasi pine is one of the most distributed pines in Asia. Its range extends south and east from the Khasi hills in the northeast Indian state of Meghalaya from where it got its name to ... Wikipedia

Juniperus blancoi.label: Juniperus blancoi
Juniperus blancoi.description:
Juniperus blancoi is a species of conifer in the Cupressaceae family.
It is endemic and found only in Mexico. Wikipedia

Mexican White Pine.label: Pinus ayacahuite
Mexican White Pine.description: Pinus ayacahuite, also called ayacahuite pine and Mexican white pine, is a species of pine native to the mountains of southern Mexico and western Central America, in the Sierra Madre del Sur and the ... Wikipedia

Orizaba Pinyon.label: Pinus orizabensis
Orizaba Pinyon.description: Pinus orizabensis, the Orizaba pinyon, is a pine in the pinyon pine group, endemic to central Mexico. It is considered also as a sub-species of Pinus cembroides which is classified as Pinus cembroides subsp. orizabensis D.K.Bailey. Wikipedia

Pinus amamiana.label: Pinus amamiana
Pinus amamiana.description: The Yakushima white pine is a native of southern Japan, on the islands of Yakushima and Tanegashima south of Kyūshū. It has also been grown horticulturally in Japanese parks. This pine can grow to a height of 25 m with a trunk diameter of up to 1 m. Wikipedia

Pinus arizonica.label: Pinus arizonica
Pinus arizonica.description: Pinus arizonica, commonly known as the Arizona pine, is a medium-sized pine in northern Mexico, southeast Arizona, southwest New Mexico, and western Texas in the United States. It is a tree growing to 25-35 m tall, with a trunk diameter of up 1.2 m. Wikipedia

Pinus bhutanica.label: Pinus bhutanica
Pinus bhutanica.description: Pinus bhutanica, which may be called the Bhutan white pine, is a tree restricted to Bhutan and adjacent parts of northeast India and southwest China. Along with the related Pinus wallichiana it is a constituent of lower altitude blue pine forests. Wikipedia

Pinus bungeana.label: Lacebark Pine
Pinus bungeana.description: Pinus bungeana English Lacebark pine; Chinese 白皮松 Japanese シロマツ is a pine tree native to northeastern and central China. It is also known as white-barked pine. Wikipedia

Pinus echinata.label: Pinus echinata
Pinus echinata.description: Pinus echinata is a species of pine native to the eastern United States from southern New York south to northern Florida, west to the extreme southeast of Kansas, and southwest to eastern Texas. Wikipedia

Pinus elliottii.label: Pinus elliottii
Pinus elliottii.description: Pinus elliottii, commonly known as the slash pine, is a pine native to the southeastern United States, from southern South Carolina west to southeastern Louisiana, and south to the Florida Keys. Wikipedia

Pinus fenzeliana.label: Pinus fenzeliana
Pinus fenzeliana.description: Pinus fenzeliana commonly known as the Hainan white pine or Fenzel's pine, is a tree endemic to the island of Hainan off southern China. This pine reaches heights of 20 m with a trunk 1 m in diameter. Wikipedia

Pinus gerardiana.label: Chilgoza Pine
Pinus gerardiana.description: Pinus gerardiana, known as the Chilgoza pine, 'noosa', or 'neoza', is a pine native to the northwestern Himalaya in eastern Afghanistan, Pakistan, and northwest India, growing at elevations between 1800–3350 m. Wikipedia

Pinus johannis.label: Pinus johannis
Pinus johannis.description: Pinus johannis is a pine in the pinyon pine group, native to North America. The range extends from southeast Arizona and southwest New Mexico, United States, south in Mexico along the Sierra Madre ... Wikipedia

Pinus koraiensis.label: Korean Pine
Pinus koraiensis.description: The tree species Pinus koraiensis is commonly called Korean pine. It is native to eastern Asia Korea, Manchuria, Mongolia, far eastern Russia, and central Japan. Wikipedia

Pinus maximinoi.label: Pinus maximinoi
Pinus maximinoi.description: Pinus maximinoi, commonly known as thinleaf pine, is a species of conifer in the Pinaceae family. It is found in El Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, and Mexico at elevations of 1,500–2,400 m. Wikipedia

Pinus leiophylla.label: Pinus leiophylla
Pinus leiophylla.description: Pinus leiophylla, commonly known as Chihuahua pine, smooth-leaf pine, and yellow pine, is a tree with a range primarily in Mexico, with a small extension into the United States in southeast Arizona and southwest New Mexico. Wikipedia

Pinus sabiniana.label: California Foothill Pine
Pinus sabiniana.description: Pinus sabiniana, with the common names gray pine, California foothill pine, and the more historically and internationally used digger pine, is a pine endemic to California in the United States. Wikipedia

Pinus montezumae.label: Pinus montezumae
Pinus montezumae.description: Pinus montezumae, known as the Montezuma pine, is a species of conifer in the family Pinaceae. It is native to Mexico and Central America, where it is known as ocote. Wikipedia

Pinus thunbergii.label: Pinus thunbergii
Pinus thunbergii.description: Pinus thunbergii is a pine native to coastal areas of Japan and South Korea. Wikipedia

Pinus serotina.label: Pinus serotina
Pinus serotina.description: Pinus serotina is a tree found along the Atlantic coastal plain of the eastern United States, from southern New Jersey south to Florida and west to southern Alabama. Wikipedia

Pinus virginiana.label: Pinus virginiana
Pinus virginiana.description: Pinus virginiana is a medium-sized tree, often found on poorer soils from Long Island in southern New York south through the Appalachian Mountains to western Tennessee and Alabama. Wikipedia

Sumatran Pine.label: Pinus merkusii
Sumatran Pine.description: Pinus merkusii, the Sumatran pine, is a pine native to the Malesia region of southeast Asia, mainly in Indonesia in the mountains of northern Sumatra, and with two outlying populations in central Sumatra ... Wikipedia

Tsuga diversifolia.label: Tsuga diversifolia
Tsuga diversifolia.description: Tsuga diversifolia, commonly known as the Northern Japanese Hemlock, or in Japanese, Kometsuga, is a species of conifer native to the Japanese islands of Honshū, Kyūshū, and Shikoku. Wikipedia

Voltziales.label: Voltziales
Voltziales.description: Voltziales is an extinct order of trees related to modern conifers. In the fossil record, the most common member of the order is Walchia, known originally for its leaf form genus, and the order is commonly called Walchian. Wikipedia

Tenasserim Pine.label: Pinus latteri
Tenasserim Pine.description: Pinus latteri, or Tenasserim pine,is a pine native to Mainland Southeast Asia. It grows in the mountains of southeastern Burma, northern Thailand, Laos, Cambodia, Vietnam, and on the Chinese island of Hainan. Wikipedia
